TP/TC_CONTENT: With a holistic approach towards enabling a strong skill development system, the Lifecycle of Training Partner and Training Centre is aimed at building a quality assured process, meeting the required parameters of the Training Provider(s) and the Training Centre(s). To achieve this objective, NSDC provides a single-window clearance system to the Training Providers (TPs) with the following features:
TP/TC_CONTENT_L1: Transparent, unified, one-stop solution with mandated time-bound delivery of accreditation and affiliation of Training Centres
TP/TC_CONTENT_L2: Single, front-end portal interface for Training Providers, ensuring accessibility to Sector Skill Councils (SSCs) and Schemes
TP/TC_CONTENT_L3: Providing opportunity to stakeholders to perform continuous technology-driven monitoring of the Training Centres
TP/TC_CONTENT_L4: Evaluating the performance of skill development programs objectively, to foster excellence and build effectiveness while delivering competency-based training
TP/TC_CONTENT_L5: Enabling the trainees and other stakeholders to make informed choices regarding Training Centres
TOT/TOA_CONTENT: Takshashila, the National Portal for Trainers and Assessors, is an initiative by NSDC under the Skill India Mission. The portal serves as a dedicated online platform for management of Trainers and Assessors of the Indian Skill ecosystem, functioning as the central repository of information concerning development of quality Trainers and Assessors. It aims to smoothly implement the Training of Trainers and Assessors requirement of skilling in India, ensuring transparency to all the involved stakeholders. The portal provides information about training programs planned by Sector Skill Councils for trainers and assessors through a public training calendar. It also provides a list of certified trainers and assessors being trained by Sector Skill Councils across states, sectors and job roles.
TOT/TOA_CONTENT_L_HEAD: Some key features of the portal are –
TOT/TOA_CONTENT_L1: Single window access to information related to trainers’ and assessors’ training calendar, certification process, competency enhancement and learning resources
TOT/TOA_CONTENT_L2: Offers transparent and structured training programs for Trainers and Assessors
TOT/TOA_CONTENT_L3: Enhances efficiency for the involved stakeholders
TOT/TOA_CONTENT_L4: Demand aggregation of TOT-TOA requirements through Training Requests

QP_NOS_CONTENT: NSDC aims to catalyze skilling initiatives that can potentially have a multiplier effect in the economy, while striving to involve the industry in all aspects of skill development. The Quality Assurance team at NSDC focuses on enabling standardized structure and consistency across the skilling endeavours in the country. All skill training programs must adhere to the National Occupational Standards (NOS) as per the constitution of the targeted Qualification Pack (QP). To assure quality and consistency of skilling across the training initiatives for the varied job roles across the country, NSDC coordinates with the respective Sector Skill Councils (SSCs) for the development of the following deliverables basis Qualification Pack amongst other resources:

SECTOR_SKILL_COUNCILS_CONTENT1: Since its inception, Sector Skill Councils (SSCs) are one of NSDC’s significant pillars of strength, which play a vital role in bridging the gap between industry demand and the skill ecosystem. Playing an instrumental role, SSCs bring together all the stakeholders - industry, labour and academia together to ensure that the industry is furnished with skilled and efficient workforce. Operating as an autonomous body, a Sector Skill Council is registered as a Section 8 Company, or a Society. NSDC initiates and incubates SSCs with initial seed funding to facilitate their growth and enable them to achieve self-sustainability in a time-bound manner.
SECTOR_SKILL_COUNCILS_CONTENT2: To facilitate employment, Sector Skill Councils have been encouraged to develop their own placement portal and mobile applications. These portals are linked to demand aggregation and are aimed at mapping the skill needs of the industry. The 360-degree interface of the portal connects candidates and training partners with recruitment firms and potential employers. Some of the SSCs have already started operating such portals, while a few others would follow.

PMKVY_HEADING: Pradhan Mantri Kaushal Vikas Yojana (PMKVY) is the flagship scheme of the Ministry of Skill Development & Entrepreneurship (MSDE). The objective of this Skill Certification Scheme is to enable a large number of Indian youth to take up industry-relevant skill training that will help them in securing a better livelihood. Individuals with prior learning experience or skills will also be assessed and certified under Recognition of Prior Learning (RPL).

We, National Skill Development Corporation, with registered office at 301, 3rd Floor, West Wing Worldmark 1, Aerocity, New Delhi -110037 (hereinafter referred to as NSDC) value your trust & respect your privacy. Note: Our privacy policy is subject to change and will periodically be updated to ensure we comply with all relevant statutory regulations as well as UDAI guidelines. Thus, we request you to review the policy periodically.
General
By using this interface and login and accessing the database system you expressly give us consent to use & disclose your personal information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree to the terms of the policy, please do not use or access this portal/database and do not accept the terms and conditions for use of this database. For the purposes of this policy “Personal Information” shall have the meaning as assigned to the term “Sensitive Data and Personal Information” in Rule 3 of Information Technology (Reasonable security practices and procedures and sensitive personal information) Rules, 2011 Periodically, NSDC may publish and share progress reports or other information reports with its oversight body with general statistical information about users of its database, such as number of students, training centers, training partners, performances of schemes etc. However, we will ensure that Sensitive Data is not published. However, by accepting this policy we understand that we have your express approval to publish any personally identifiable data to help smooth facilitation of NSDC schemes.
Collection of Personal Information
Personal Information (see meaning assigned in 1.2 above) includes all information that can be linked to a specific individual or to identify any individual such as Aadhaar number, name, address, mailing address, telephone number, email ID, bank account details and any details that may have been voluntarily provided by the user of NSDC scheme and non scheme based services, in connection with availing benefits of providing or using such training When you use this portal, you will be providing us Personal Information, willingly with the full understanding that these details are required for the purpose mentioned below. You are requested not to provide us with personal data of persons other than yourselves, unless you have collected the data only after (i) informing them of the purpose for which data is collected (ii) the manner in which the data is collected used and stored (iii) and the data is collected through a secure and encrypted system
Use of Personal Information
NSDC shall ask you to provide Personal Information only for lawful purpose connected with our Services and necessary to be collected by us for such purpose.  NSDC can collect and uses personal information
Disclosure of Personal Information
NSDC does not sell, rent or trade the information we have collected about you, other than as disclosed within this Privacy Policy or at the time you provide your information. By accepting these term and conditions, we understand that we have your express consent to share information disclosed by you with third parties, for the purposes of providing NSDC services. Following are some instances when information may be shared:
Change of Information or correction of details
You are responsible for maintaining the accuracy of the information you submit to us. If your Personal Information changes you may correct, delete inaccuracies, or amend information by making the change through this secure SDMS portal. If upon modifying or changing the information earlier provided to NSDC, we find it difficult to permit access to our Services to you due to insufficiency/ inaccuracy of the information, we may, in our sole discretion terminate your access to the services by providing you by NSDC.
Cookies
A ""cookie"" is a small piece of information stored by a web server on a web browser so it can be later read back from that browser. This SDMS uses cookie and tracking technology depending on the features offered. No personal information will be collected via cookies and other tracking technology; however, if you previously provided personally identifiable information, cookies may be tied to such information. Aggregate cookie and tracking information may be shared with third parties.
Links to Other Sites
This SDMS limits hyperlinking. However, there may be few instances where SDMS or the website offering SDMS access links to other websites. These other websites that may collect personally identifiable information about you. NSDC is not responsible for the privacy practices or the content of those linked websites.
Security
NSDC has stringent security measures in place to protect the loss, misuse, and alteration of the information under our control. Once your information is in our possession we adhere to strict security guidelines, protecting it against unauthorized access.
